Libraries/Tools Used:
	I used the cryptography library in python. 
I used this instead of PyCryptdome because after reviewing documentation it seemed easier and more straightforward for me. 
Specifically some of the imports were PBKDF2HMAC, hashes, and AESGCM. 
PBKDF2HMAC was used for turning the password into a cryptographic key. 
Hashes.SHA256() was used as the hashing algorithm. 
AESGCM was used to do the actual encryption and decryption of the files. 
During development I found nonce which stands for number only used once. 
This allows a one-time generated number to be used in the encryption. 
Another tool that was used was using flag bytes that helped it identify how an encrypted file was encrypted. 
For example if it was encrypted with a password. 
The AES key length bytes were 16/24/32 these were the lengths of the keys.
Salting was also used for passwords to prevent 2 passwords from having the same value. 
Using urandom gives each password a random salted value. 
Also used much documentation from the cryptography.io page and many youtube videos.

